ative to their actual likelihood of success.\n\nAcademic research also highlight
s AI\'s potential to exploit systematic biases. A study by LiveTradeBench\n\nin 
dynamic trading environments, revealing that models with high LMArena scores did
not always outperform others in real-world scenarios. Instead, success hinged on
a model\'s risk appetite and ability to adapt to evolving market conditions. Thi
s underscores the importance of tailored AI strategies, where machine learning a
lgorithms are trained on historical prediction market data to optimize for speci
fic outcomes.\n\n### Challenges and Risks: Artificial Trading and Regulatory Scr
utiny\n\nDespite the promise, AI-driven prediction markets face significant chal
