trust in the integrity of predictions. For example, a controversial market on Uk
rainian President Zelenskyy\'s attire\n\nbut sparked debates over resolution cri
teria, highlighting the risks of subjective event definitions.\n\nRegulatory scr
utiny is another hurdle. While Kalshi\'s CFTC compliance provides a clear legal 
framework, Polymarket\'s recent U.S. relaunch has raised questions about oversig
ht. The integration of blockchain-based oracles, such as UMA Protocol (which und
erpins 80% of Polymarket\'s subjective markets),\n\n. Additionally, the smaller 
liquidity pools in prediction markets compared to traditional financial instrume
nts\n\nto execute large trades without slippage.\n\n---\n\nTitle: The Economics 
